PROJECT DESCRIPTION
-------------------
NeurologiqueTWIN is an original research and engineering project
combining multimodal deep learning, digital twin state machines,
and multi-agent emergency simulation for neurological seizure
risk monitoring. The project encompasses:

  - ResNet-CBAM deep learning models (GASF / MTF / Recurrence Plot)
    trained on the SeizeIT2 epilepsy dataset — 90% classification accuracy
  - Explainable risk scoring with SHAP-style feature attribution
  - Markov-chain digital twin for real-time patient state estimation
  - Multi-agent Mesa simulation (Patient / WatchTwin / Dispatcher / Ambulance)
  - Clinical NLP (DistilBERT zero-shot + TF-IDF fallback)
  - XGBoost tabular model on 20-dimensional EEG + IMU features
  - CWGAN-GP synthetic EEG data generation
  - FastAPI REST backend (27 endpoints) + Next.js 15 frontend (9 pages)
  - Brain digital twin SVG viewer (20 anatomical regions, axial + lateral)
  - Docker Compose one-command deployment

